snippet: The charges seemed to extinguish hope of a political resolution that would bring the Muslim Brotherhood out from underground and back into the political process.
abstract: Egypt’s chief prosecutor orders former president Mohamed Morsi and other Muslim Brotherhood leaders to stand trial on charges including inciting murder; order seems to extinguish hope of a political resolution that would bring Muslim Brotherhood out from underground and back into political process.

byline.contributor: David D. Kirkpatrick and Mayy El Sheikh contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: The charges seemed to extinguish hope of a political resolution that would bring the Muslim Brotherhood out from underground and back into the political process.
